<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Trail on The Flying Scotts</title><link>https://www.flying-scotts.uk/pr-preview/pr-17/tags/trail/</link><description>Recent content in Trail on The Flying Scotts</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-gb</language><managingEditor>user@example.com (Chris Scott)</managingEditor><webMaster>user@example.com (Chris Scott)</webMaster><copyright>2026 The Flying Scotts</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sat, 17 Dec 2016 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.flying-scotts.uk/pr-preview/pr-17/tags/trail/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Great Barrier Island</title><link>https://www.flying-scotts.uk/pr-preview/pr-17/2016/12/17/great-barrier-island/</link><pubDate>Sat, 17 Dec 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>user@example.com (Chris Scott)</author><guid>https://www.flying-scotts.uk/pr-preview/pr-17/2016/12/17/great-barrier-island/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;I was lucky enough to go on a trip to &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Barrier_Island"&gt;Great Barrier Island&lt;/a&gt; with some friends from work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="post-photos"&gt;
&lt;a data-index="0" data-size="1920x1425" data-title="Small plane" href="https://www.flying-scotts.uk/pr-preview/pr-17/2016/12/17/great-barrier-island/001_small-plane.jpg"&gt;
&lt;img src="https://www.flying-scotts.uk/pr-preview/pr-17/2016/12/17/great-barrier-island/001_small-plane_hu_917016c7e9dca300.jpg" class="img-fluid-both rounded mx-auto d-block" title="Small plane" alt="Small plane" /&gt;
&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It was the first time I had been on a small plane but fortunately the weather was perfect and it was a very smooth ride with some incredible views.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="post-photos"&gt;
&lt;a data-index="0" data-size="1920x1280" data-title="On the way to Great Barrier" href="https://www.flying-scotts.uk/pr-preview/pr-17/2016/12/17/great-barrier-island/002_flying-over.jpg"&gt;
&lt;img src="https://www.flying-scotts.uk/pr-preview/pr-17/2016/12/17/great-barrier-island/002_flying-over_hu_66fc19e10118ad4a.jpg" class="img-fluid-both rounded mx-auto d-block" title="On the way to Great Barrier" alt="On the way to Great Barrier" /&gt;
&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On Great Barrier we walked to Mount Hobson, starting along &lt;a href="http://www.doc.govt.nz/parks-and-recreation/places-to-go/auckland/places/great-barrier-island-aotea/things-to-do/tracks/kaitoke-hot-springs-track/"&gt;Kaitoke Hot Springs Track&lt;/a&gt;, then heading east along Tramline Track before heading left at the fork with Peach Tree Track and up to &lt;a href="http://www.doc.govt.nz/parks-and-recreation/places-to-go/auckland/places/great-barrier-island-aotea/things-to-do/mt-heale-hut/"&gt;Mt Heale Hut&lt;/a&gt;. From there it was a short but very steep up to Mount Hobson and some incredible views over the island.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Queenstown Hill</title><link>https://www.flying-scotts.uk/pr-preview/pr-17/2016/2/8/queenstown-hill/</link><pubDate>Mon, 08 Feb 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>user@example.com (Chris Scott)</author><guid>https://www.flying-scotts.uk/pr-preview/pr-17/2016/2/8/queenstown-hill/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;After two weeks in New Zealand I was lucky enough to go to a conference in Queenstown.
Before the conference started we went for a run/walk up Queenstown Hill, which has some great views overlooking the lake.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="post-photos"&gt;
&lt;a data-index="0" data-size="1920x1425" data-title="Lake Wakatipu from Queenstown Hill" href="https://www.flying-scotts.uk/pr-preview/pr-17/2016/2/8/queenstown-hill/002_queenstown-hill.jpg"&gt;
&lt;img src="https://www.flying-scotts.uk/pr-preview/pr-17/2016/2/8/queenstown-hill/002_queenstown-hill_hu_aa9ad7a550541f78.jpg" class="img-fluid-both rounded mx-auto d-block" title="Lake Wakatipu from Queenstown Hill" alt="Lake Wakatipu from Queenstown Hill" /&gt;
&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
